cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.SD

This paper is about identifying fake samples generated by the Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) framework. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary field of GANs. The paper also discusses statistical analysis and comparison of raw pixel values and features extracted from them, which falls under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses learning formal specifications from real data, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the violation of specifications, which is related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SD (Sound).
